    "rawText": "Skip To Main Content\nWelcome To Campus Sanofi PH\n\nDo you already have an account on Campus Sanofi Philippines?\nSign in to receive personalized recommendations\n\nRegister\nLog in\nBrowse the latest medical information\nDIABETES\nLEARN\n\nMay 18, 2026\n\nE-learning Course – Foundations of Diabetes Management\nLearn more\nCARDIOLOGY\nREAD\n\nMay 12, 2026\n\nAntihypertensive Adherence \u0026 Persistence with ARBs\n\nExplore how ARBs improve adherence and persistence in hypertension treatment vs other therapies.\n\nLearn more\nCARDIOLOGY\nREAD\n\nApr 22, 2026\n\nHypertension Management Updates\n\nLatest ACC 2026 congress insights on hypertension management, single-pill combinations, blood pressure variability, and cardiovascular outcomes\n\nLearn more\nINFLUENZA\n\nMar 19, 2026\n\nHow to Use: Pre-filled Syringe with Luer lock and soft tip cap\n\nWatch step-by-step video guide on using pre-filled syringe with Luer Lock adapter for influenza vaccine administration. Proper technique tutorial.\n\nLearn more\nINFLUENZA\nREAD\n\nMar 19, 2026\n\nOver 70 Years of Leadership in Influenza Vaccines\n\nSanofi has been at the forefront of influenza vaccine development for over 70 years, delivering more than 5 billion doses across 100+ countries and immunizing over 250 million people annually. With a robust global network of production sites spanning Canada, France, Mexico, the United States, Australia, and China, Sanofi continues to invest in cutting-edge R\u0026D across egg-based, recombinant, and mRNA platforms — ensuring the world gets the right shot against flu\n\nLearn more\nCARDIOLOGY\nREAD\n\nMar 10, 2026\n\nManaging Nocturnal Hypertension: Key Insights from the Asian Expert Consensus\n\nExplore key recommendations from the Asian Expert Consensus on Nocturnal Hypertension Management, covering diagnosis, epidemiology, cardiovascular risks, and treatment strategies — including lifestyle modifications and long-acting antihypertensive agents — to guide optimal nighttime blood pressure control in clinical practice.\n\nLearn more\nDIABETES\n\nJan 6, 2026\n\nMedical-on-the-Go:\n\nPeriodontitis: the oft-overlooked complication of diabetes\n\nLearn more\nDIABETES\nREAD\n\nDec 29, 2025\n\nMedical-On-The-Go: The Soli-SWITCH study\n\nSwitching from premixed insulin to iGlarLixi in people with Type 2 diabetes\n\nLearn more\nWhat\u0027s new in Campus?\nStart Learning Now\nGo to Facebook Page\nMore about Science\nDiabetes\nCardiology\nNephrology\nThrombosis\nDiphtheria\nHaemophilus Influenza Type B\nInfluenza\nInvasive Meningococcal Disease\nPertussis\nPoliomyelitis\nTetanus\nFor General Inquires – Contact us\n \n\nAdverse events \u0026 product safety\n\nIf you experience any adverse event, i.e., any unfavorable and unintended sign (an abnormal laboratory finding), symptom, or disease temporarily associated with the use of a medical product, please email it to PV.Philippines@sanofi.com \n\n\n \n\nTo report a product technical complaint, please contact our Quality Affairs team:\n\n \n\nVoicemail (non-business hours): +632-8859-5555 extension #1\nEmail: Philippines.PTC@sanofi.com\n\n \n\n \n\nFor Pharma Medical inquiries, click HERE to submit a question. \n\nFor Vaccine Medical inquiries, send an email to: medinfo.vaccines.ph@sanofi.com\n\n \n\n \n\nFor Data Privacy requests and concerns:\n \n\nSanofi General Medicines (under sanofi-aventis Philippines, Inc.)\nData Privacy: privacy.PH@sanofi.com\n \nFor Data subject requests:\nSanofi General Medicines (under sanofi-aventis Philippines, Inc.): OneTrust\nFor General Inquires – Contact us\n \n\nAdverse events \u0026 product safety\n\nIf you experience any adverse event, i.e., any unfavorable and unintended sign (an abnormal laboratory finding), symptom, or disease temporarily associated with the use of a medical product, please email it to PV.Philippines@sanofi.com \n\n\n \n\nTo report a product technical complaint, please contact our Quality Affairs team:\n\n \n\nVoicemail (non-business hours): +632-8859-5555 extension #1\nEmail: Philippines.PTC@sanofi.com\n\n \n\n \n\nFor Pharma Medical inquiries, click HERE to submit a question. \n\nFor Vaccine Medical inquiries, send an email to: medinfo.vaccines.ph@sanofi.com\n\n \n\n \n\nFor Data Privacy requests and concerns:\n \n\nSanofi General Medicines (under sanofi-aventis Philippines, Inc.)\nData Privacy: privacy.PH@sanofi.com\n \nFor Data subject requests:\nSanofi General Medicines (under sanofi-aventis Philippines, Inc.): OneTrust",
